{"TopicId":198394,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Making a ramp for the Mk3 bay","CreatedByName":"Fierce Wolf","CreatedById":200019,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-11-28T16:29:35Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Fierce Wolf","CreatedById":200019,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-11-28T16:29:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHello guys!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have been trying for an automatic ramp to deploy a rover from a lander that has an mk3 bay, however, multiple designs have failed. So far i just disengage the landing legs, have the bay touch the ground and deploy, but it SUCKS.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny ideas? Have you tried it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00223333.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002275.80\u0022 height=\u0022589\u0022 width=\u0022777\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/ChVR0dS/3333.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Streetwind","CreatedById":98962,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-11-28T16:31:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe proper Kerbal solution would be to attach boosters to the rover and have it launch out of the cargo bay like a bat out of hell \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/kerbal-forum-uploads/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Fierce Wolf","CreatedById":200019,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-11-28T16:46:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI kinda did, but with monoprop, the problem is that i use that monop to speed up the rover in boring parts\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Serenity","CreatedById":179192,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-11-28T17:16:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223887392\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022198394\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221606581995\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022200019\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Fierce Wolf\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n30 minutes ago, Fierce Wolf said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI kinda did, but with monoprop, the problem is that i use that monop to speed up the rover in boring parts\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDid you know you can clip two cargo bays or even more to make an even bigger one?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd doesn\u0027t look or feel cheaty, its almost by design, just try to clip two with open cargo bays and eventually you will see what i mean \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E .\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-11-28T17:17:42Z\u0022 title=\u002211/28/2020 05:17  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 28, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Boyster\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Fierce Wolf","CreatedById":200019,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-11-28T18:14:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223887403\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022198394\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221606583777\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022179192\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Boyster\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n58 minutes ago, Boyster said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDid you know you can clip two cargo bays or even more to make an even bigger one?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Rajini-meme-Aus-police.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002266.53\u0022 height=\u0022499\u0022 width=\u0022750\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.thenewsminute.com/sites/default/files/Rajini-meme-Aus-police.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"18Watt","CreatedById":198538,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-11-28T22:06:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPerhaps a hinge with a flat panel attached to it. \u00A0Hinges are in the Breaking Ground expansion.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"king of nowhere","CreatedById":204876,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-11-29T11:45:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\na hinge with a flat panel works, but it is incredibly heavy, results in a steep slope that most rovers can\u0027t climb, and is often unstable.\u00A0 I tried it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI had some success with a robotic arm made of some hinges to pick up and deploy a rover.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthere is a ramp piece, but the entrance is fairly narrow, meaning it cannot accomodate a large rover.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nand all those solutions are frustratingly expensive\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}